Kiess's Roc Road escort function is the most demanding active operational environment for Crusader practitioners in the five-city network. The frontier context provides actual tactical engagements against route predators — where both Knight formation discipline and Swordsman individual excellence are tested against opponents who have adapted to both in isolation and must now face them combined. Wall Command rates Crusader capability above either parent tradition for convoy escort in contested terrain: formation discipline for ambush response, individual escalating momentum for close-quarters pursuit phases. The Anti Magic Shell is valued in Roc Road contexts because route predators in the eastern frontier zone increasingly employ magical disruption as a first-contact technique.

