Khephari cyclical-durability doctrine — the understanding that what endures does so through structural soundness tested repeatedly over time rather than peak performance under ideal conditions — maps naturally onto the Crusader Corps' founding insight. The Solar Court's original campaign-honor title recognized practitioners who remained structurally sound through continuous successive engagements; the Crusader Corps synthesis doctrine produces practitioners who are more structurally sound under varied conditions than practitioners trained in a single approach. Khephari practitioners entering the Crusader tradition through Kiess's Roc Road operational environment find the tradition's combination of defensive resilience and sustained momentum aligns with their cultural framework for endurance through structural testing.
